data.title: Very Good Cantonese Food
data.text: We have been visiting Toy's for many years and it has been consistently good for Cantonese food.  We had a family dinner for seven and had many dishes - Seafood Tofu Soup, Shredded Pork with Bean Sprouts over Pan Fried Noodles, green beans with beef, pot stickers, Moo Shu Pork, fried chicken wings and steamed pork with salted fish (which is not on the menu but they will prepare on request). Everything was prepared very well and served piping hot - the same way it has been served for many years.  The meal was enjoyed by the entire family, even the two small children.  We hope to continue to visit this restaurant for many years to come.

data.title: Very crowded with Asians, a good sign
data.text: Had combos. Generous servings. Third visit. Seattle celebrities often here. No wait but a very busy Tuesday. Always follow the crowd.

data.title: Chinese food delivery
data.text:
The delivery was quck - less than an hour.
The food was very bland!  
Snow peas were way over cooked.
The sweet and sour chicken had no flavor!  
Same sauce for the fried prawns appetizer and the sweet/sour chicken...
No rice included (thought it would be).
